"decision_type": "heuristic", "previous_command": "auto-deps", "code_exists": false, "regenerate_after_autodeps": true, "budget_remaining": 20.0, "llm_trace": {"prompt": "[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"You are an expert Python 3.12 engineer. Follow these project conventions:\\n- Use type hints on all public functions.\\n- Use dataclasses or TypedDict for simple records; avoid heavy frameworks.\\n- Prefer pathlib over os.path.\\n- Use pytest for tests; one assertion per logical behavior.\\n- No print() in library code; raise exceptions or return values.\\n- Keep modules small and cohesive.\\n\\nTesting conventions:\\n- Use pytest only; do not use Z3, hypothesis, or formal verification frameworks.\\n- Every test must correspond to a documented requirement. No tautologies.\\n- Prefer direct assertions over property-based solvers.\\n- Never wrap imports in try/except ImportError: pass. Let import errors propagate.\\n- Do not add defensive stubs for \\\"environments where the dependency isn't present.\\\"\\n\\n\\n<pdd-reason>\\nFlask web app for Study Quest, a gamified prompt-driven study tracker.\\nThe web app provides a polished dashboard for interview demos.\\n</pdd-reason>\\n\\n<pdd-interface>\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"web_app\\\",\\n  \\\"framework\\\": \\\"flask\\\",\\n  \\\"routes\\\": [\\n    {\\\"path\\\": \\\"/\\\", \\\"method\\\": \\\"GET\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Dashboard\\\"},\\n    {\\\"path\\\": \\\"/sessions\\\", \\\"method\\\": \\\"GET\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"List sessions\\\"},\\n    {\\\"path\\\": \\\"/sessions/add\\\", \\\"method\\\": \\\"GET\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Show add session form\\\"},\\n    {\\\"path\\\": \\\"/sessions/add\\\", \\\"method\\\": \\\"POST\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Create a new session\\\"},\\n    {\\\"path\\\": \\\"/sessions/delete/<session_id>\\\", \\\"method\\\": \\\"POST\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Delete a session\\\"},\\n    {\\\"path\\\": \\\"/demo-reset\\\", \\\"method\\\": \\\"POST\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Seed demo data\\\"}\\n  ]\\n}\\n</pdd-interface>\\n\\n<pdd-dependency>session_store_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>\\n<pdd-dependency>quest_engine_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>\\n\\n% Role & Scope\\nBuild a small Flask web app for demoing Study Quest.\\nThe app should look polished, modern, and useful while remaining simple enough for PDD-generated code.\\n\\n% Application Behavior\\n1. Expose a Flask application object named `app`.\\n2. Store path defaults to ~/.study_tracker/sessions.json.\\n3. Store path can be configured through an environment variable named STUDY_TRACKER_STORE.\\n4. Daily goal defaults to 120 minutes.\\n5. Daily goal can be configured through an environment variable named STUDY_TRACKER_DAILY_GOAL.\\n6. The app should be runnable with:\\n   python -m src.web_app\\n\\n% Routes\\n\\n1. GET `/`\\n   - Shows the main dashboard.\\n   - Includes:\\n     - total minutes\\n     - today minutes\\n     - daily goal progress\\n     - streak days\\n     - favorite topic\\n     - achievements\\n     - daily quests\\n     - suggestion from summary[\\\"suggestion\\\"]\\n     - recent sessions\\n   - Uses session_store.summarize.\\n   - Uses session_store.list_sessions.\\n   - Uses quest_engine.generate_daily_quests.\\n\\n2. GET `/sessions`\\n   - Shows all sessions in reverse chronological order.\\n   - Each session displays:\\n     - topic\\n     - minutes\\n     - mood\\n     - notes\\n     - created_at\\n     - delete button\\n\\n3. GET `/sessions/add`\\n   - Shows a form with:\\n     - topic\\n     - minutes\\n     - mood\\n     - notes\\n\\n4. POST `/sessions/add`\\n   - Validates submitted form data.\\n   - Calls session_store.add_session.\\n   - Redirects to `/` on success.\\n   - Shows a friendly error message on ValueError.\\n\\n5. POST `/sessions/delete/<session_id>`\\n   - Calls session_store.delete_session.\\n   - Redirects to `/sessions`.\\n\\n6. POST `/demo-reset`\\n   - Calls session_store.seed_demo_data.\\n   - Redirects to `/`.\\n\\n% UI Requirements\\n1. Use Jinja templates.\\n2. Use a base template with a navigation bar.\\n3. Use simple CSS from static/styles.css.\\n4. Do not require JavaScript for core functionality.\\n5. The dashboard should feel like a modern productivity app.\\n6. Use visual cards for:\\n   - Today's progress\\n   - Streak\\n   - Favorite topic\\n   - Badges\\n7. Show a progress bar for daily goal completion.\\n8. Show quests as checklist-style cards.\\n9. Use emojis sparingly for demo polish:\\n   - \ud83d\udcda dashboard\\n   - \ud83d\udd25 streak\\n   - \ud83c\udfc6 achievements\\n   - \ud83c\udfaf goal\\n   - \u2705 completed quest\\n10. Keep HTML semantic and readable.\\n\\n% Demo Flow\\nThe web app should support this live demo:\\n1. Start app.\\n2. Click \\\"Load Demo Data\\\".\\n3. Show dashboard progress, streaks, quests, and achievements.\\n4. Add a new session.\\n5. Return to dashboard and show updated progress.\\n6. Open sessions page and show stored history.\\n\\n% Quality Requirements\\n1. Keep route functions small.\\n2. Keep business logic in session_store and quest_engine.\\n3. Do not duplicate summary logic in the web app.\\n4. Keep behavior deterministic and easy to test.\\n5. Avoid unnecessary dependencies.\"}]", "response": "```python\n# src/models.py\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any, Optional\n\n@dataclass(frozen=True)\nclass Session:\n    session_id: str\n    topic: str\n    minutes: int\n    mood: str\n    notes: str\n    created_at: str\n\n@dataclass(frozen=True)\nclass Summary:\n    total_minutes: int\n    today_minutes: int\n    daily_goal: int\n    streak_days: int\n    favorite_topic: str\n    achievements: List[str]\n    suggestion: str\n\n@dataclass(frozen=True)\nclass Quest:\n    title: str\n    description: str\n    reward: str\n    is_completed: bool\n```\n\n```python\n# src/session_store.py\nimport json\nimport os\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime, date\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any\nimport uuid\n\nclass SessionStore:\n    def __init__(self, storage_path: Path, daily_goal: int = 120):\n        self.storage_path = storage_path\n        self.daily_goal = daily_goal\n        self._ensure_storage()\n\n    def _ensure_storage(self) -> None:\n        self.storage_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n        if not self.storage_path.exists():\n            self._save_data([])\n\n    def _load_data(self) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n        try:\n            with open(self.storage_path, \"r\") as f:\n                return json.load(f)\n        except (json.JSONDecodeError, FileNotFoundError):\n            return []\n\n    def _save_data(self, data: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n        with open(self.storage_path, \"w\") as f:\n            json.dump(data, f, indent=2)\n\n    def list_sessions(self) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n        sessions = self._load_data()\n        return sorted(sessions, key=lambda x: x[\"created_at\"], reverse=True)\n\n    def add_session(self, topic: str, minutes: int, mood: str, notes: str) -> str:\n        if minutes <= 0:\n            raise ValueError(\"Minutes must be positive.\")\n        \n        sessions = self._load_data()\n        session_id = str(uuid.uuid4())\n        new_session = {\n            \"session_id\": session_id,\n            \"topic\": topic.strip() or \"General Study\",\n            \"minutes\": minutes,\n            \"mood\": mood,\n            \"notes\": notes,\n            \"created_at\": datetime.now().isoformat()\n        }\n        sessions.append(new_session)\n        self._save_data(sessions)\n        return session_id\n\n    def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> None:\n        sessions = self._load_data()\n        filtered = [s for s in sessions if s[\"session_id\"] != session_id]\n        self._save_data(filtered)\n\n    def summarize(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        sessions = self._load_data()\n        today_str = date.today().isoformat()\n        \n        total_mins = sum(s[\"minutes\"] for s in sessions)\n        today_mins = sum(s[\"minutes\"] for s in sessions if s[\"created_at\"].startswith(today_str))\n        \n        # Simple Topic Logic\n        topics: Dict[str, int] = {}\n        for s in sessions:\n            topics[s[\"topic\"]] = topics.get(s[\"topic\"], 0) + s[\"minutes\"]\n        fav_topic = max(topics, key=topics.get) if topics else \"None\"\n\n        # Simple Streak Logic (Days with at least one session)\n        dates = sorted({s[\"created_at\"][:10] for s in sessions}, reverse=True)\n        streak = 0\n        current_check = date.today()\n        for d_str in dates:\n            d = date.fromisoformat(d_str)\n            if d == current_check:\n                streak += 1\n                current_check = date.fromordinal(current_check.toordinal() - 1)\n            elif d > current_check:\n                continue\n            else:\n                break\n        \n        achievements = []\n        if streak >= 3: achievements.append(\"3-Day Streak \ud83d\udd25\")\n        if total_mins >= 600: achievements.append(\"10-Hour Master \ud83c\udfc6\")\n        if today_mins >= self.daily_goal: achievements.append(\"Goal Crusher \ud83c\udfaf\")\n\n        suggestion = \"Time to hit the books!\" if today_mins < self.daily_goal else \"Goal reached! Great job.\"\n\n        return {\n            \"total_minutes\": total_mins,\n            \"today_minutes\": today_mins,\n            \"daily_goal\": self.daily_goal,\n            \"streak_days\": streak,\n            \"favorite_topic\": fav_topic,\n            \"achievements\": achievements,\n            \"suggestion\": suggestion\n        }\n\n    def seed_demo_data(self) -> None:\n        demo_sessions = [\n            {\"session_id\": \"d1\", \"topic\": \"Python\", \"minutes\": 45, \"mood\": \"Happy\", \"notes\": \"Learned decorators\", \"created_at\": date.today().isoformat() + \"T10:00:00\"},\n            {\"session_id\": \"d2\", \"topic\": \"Flask\", \"minutes\": 90, \"mood\": \"Focused\", \"notes\": \"Routing\", \"created_at\": date.today().isoformat() + \"T14:00:00\"},\n        ]\n        self._save_data(demo_sessions)\n```\n\n```python\n# src/quest_engine.py\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any\n\ndef generate_daily_quests(today_minutes: int, daily_goal: int) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n    return [\n        {\n            \"title\": \"Kickstart\",\n            \"description\": \"Log at least 15 minutes\",\n            \"reward\": \"10 XP\",\n            \"is_completed\": today_minutes >= 15\n        },\n        {\n            \"title\": \"Daily Goal\",\n            \"description\": f\"Reach {daily_goal} minutes\",\n            \"reward\": \"50 XP\",\n            \"is_completed\": today_minutes >= daily_goal\n        }\n    ]\n```\n\n```python\n# src/web_app.py\nimport os\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom flask import Flask, render_template, request, redirect, url_for, flash\nfrom .session_store import SessionStore\nfrom .quest_engine import generate_daily_quests\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\napp.secret_key = \"demo-secret-key\"\n\n# Configuration\nDEFAULT_STORE = Path.home() / \".study_tracker\" / \"sessions.json\"\nSTORE_PATH = Path(os.getenv(\"STUDY_TRACKER_STORE\", str(DEFAULT_STORE)))\nDAILY_GOAL = int(os.getenv(\"STUDY_TRACKER_DAILY_GOAL\", \"120\"))\n\nstore = SessionStore(STORE_PATH, daily_goal=DAILY_GOAL)\n\n@app.route(\"/\")\ndef dashboard():\n    summary = store.summarize()\n    sessions = store.list_sessions()[:5]\n    quests = generate_daily_quests(summary[\"today_minutes\"], summary[\"daily_goal\"])\n    \n    progress_percent = min(100, int((summary[\"today_minutes\"] / summary[\"daily_goal\"]) * 100))\n    \n    return render_template(\n        \"dashboard.html\",\n        summary=summary,\n        sessions=sessions,\n        quests=quests,\n        progress_percent=progress_percent\n    )\n\n@app.route(\"/sessions\")\ndef list_sessions():\n    sessions = store.list_sessions()\n    return render_template(\"sessions.html\", sessions=sessions)\n\n@app.route(\"/sessions/add\", methods=[\"GET\", \"POST\"])\ndef add_session():\n    if request.method == \"POST\":\n        try:\n            topic = request.form.get(\"topic\", \"\")\n            minutes = int(request.form.get(\"minutes\", 0))\n            mood = request.form.get(\"mood\", \"\")\n            notes = request.form.get(\"notes\", \"\")\n            \n            store.add_session(topic, minutes, mood, notes)\n            return redirect(url_for(\"dashboard\"))\n        except ValueError as e:\n            flash(str(e))\n            return render_template(\"add_session.html\"), 400\n            \n    return render_template(\"add_session.html\")\n\n@app.route(\"/sessions/delete/<session_id>\", methods=[\"POST\"])\ndef delete_session(session_id: str):\n    store.delete_session(session_id)\n    return redirect(url_for(\"list_sessions\"))\n\n@app.route(\"/demo-reset\", methods=[\"POST\"])\ndef demo_reset():\n    store.seed_demo_data()\n    return redirect(url_for(\"dashboard\"))\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    app.run(debug=True, port=5000)\n```\n\n```html\n<!-- templates/base.html -->\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Study Quest</title>\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"{{ url_for('static', filename='styles.css') }}\">\n</head>\n<body>\n    <nav class=\"navbar\">\n        <div class=\"container\">\n            <a href=\"/\" class=\"brand\">\ud83d\udcda Study Quest</a>\n            <div class=\"nav-links\">\n                <a href=\"/\">Dashboard</a>\n                <a href=\"/sessions\">Sessions</a>\n                <a href=\"/sessions/add\">Add Session</a>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </nav>\n    <main class=\"container\">\n        {% with messages = get_flashed_messages() %}\n          {% if messages %}\n            {% for message in messages %}\n              <div class=\"alert\">{{ message }}</div>\n            {% endfor %}\n          {% endif %}\n        {% endwith %}\n        {% block content %}{% endblock %}\n    </main>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n```html\n<!-- templates/dashboard.html -->\n{% extends \"base.html\" %}\n{% block content %}\n<header class=\"dashboard-header\">\n    <h1>Welcome Back!</h1>\n    <p class=\"suggestion\">\ud83d\udca1 {{ summary.suggestion }}</p>\n</header>\n\n<div class=\"grid\">\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <h3>\ud83c\udfaf Today's Goal</h3>\n        <div class=\"progress-container\">\n            <div class=\"progress-bar\" style=\"width: {{ progress_percent }}%\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <p>{{ summary.today_minutes }} / {{ summary.daily_goal }} mins</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <h3>\ud83d\udd25 Streak</h3>\n        <div class=\"stat-value\">{{ summary.streak_days }} Days</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <h3>\ud83d\udcda Top Topic</h3>\n        <div class=\"stat-value\">{{ summary.favorite_topic }}</div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n<section class=\"section-row\">\n    <div class=\"quests\">\n        <h2>Daily Quests</h2>\n        {% for quest in quests %}\n        <div class=\"quest-card {{ 'completed' if quest.is_completed else '' }}\">\n            <span>{{ '\u2705' if quest.is_completed else '\u2b1c' }}</span>\n            <div class=\"quest-info\">\n                <strong>{{ quest.title }}</strong>\n                <small>{{ quest.description }}</small>\n            </div>\n            <span class=\"reward\">{{ quest.reward }}</span>\n        </div>\n        {% endfor %}\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"achievements\">\n        <h2>\ud83c\udfc6 Achievements</h2>\n        <div class=\"badge-list\">\n            {% for badge in summary.achievements %}\n            <span class=\"badge\">{{ badge }}</span>\n            {% else %}\n            <p>No achievements yet. Keep studying!</p>\n            {% endfor %}\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>\n\n<div class=\"demo-actions\">\n    <form action=\"/demo-reset\" method=\"POST\">\n        <button type=\"submit\" class=\"btn-secondary\">Load Demo Data</button>\n    </form>\n</div>\n{% endblock %}\n```\n\n```css\n/* static/styles.css */\n:root {\n    --primary: #4f46e5;\n    --bg: #f9fafb;\n    --card: #ffffff;\n    --text: #111827;\n    --border: #e5e7eb;\n}\n\nbody { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); margin: 0; }\n.container { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 1rem; }\n.navbar { background: var(--card); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 1rem 0; margin-bottom: 2rem; }\n.navbar .container { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; padding: 0 1rem; }\n.brand { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none; color: var(--primary); }\n.nav-links a { margin-left: 1rem; text-decoration: none; color: #4b5563; }\n\n.grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }\n.card { background: var(--card); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--border); }\n.stat-value { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); }\n\n.progress-container { background: #e5e7eb; border-radius: 1rem; height: 12px; margin: 10px 0; overflow: hidden; }\n.progress-bar { background: var(--primary); height: 100%; transition: width 0.3s; }\n\n.quest-card { display: flex; align-items: center; background: var(--card); padding: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--border); }\n.quest-card.completed { opacity: 0.6; background: #f0fdf4; }\n.quest-info { flex-grow: 1; margin-left: 1rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }\n.badge { background: #fee2e2; color: #991b1b; padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 9999px; font-size: 0.875rem; display: inline-block; margin: 0.25rem; }\n\n.btn { background: var(--primary); color: white; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border: none; border-radius: 0.25rem; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none; }\n.btn-secondary { background: #f3f4f6; color: #374151; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-radius: 0.25rem; cursor: pointer; }\n\ntable { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; background: var(--card); margin-top: 1rem; }\nth, td { text-align: left; padding: 0.75rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }\nform div { margin-bottom: 1rem; }\ninput, select, textarea { width: 100%; padding: 0.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 0.25rem; }\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_web_app.py\nimport pytest\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom src.web_app import app, store\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef client(tmp_path):\n    app.config[\"TESTING\"] = True\n    test_db = tmp_path / \"test_sessions.json\"\n    store.storage_path = test_db\n    store._save_data([]) # Reset\n    with app.test_client() as client:\n        yield client\n\ndef test_dashboard_status_code(client):\n    \"\"\"The dashboard should be accessible via GET.\"\"\"\n    response = client.get(\"/\")\n    assert response.status_code == 200\n\ndef test_add_session_creates_record(client):\n    \"\"\"POSTing a valid session should redirect and persist data.\"\"\"\n    data = {\"topic\": \"Math\", \"minutes\": \"30\", \"mood\": \"Happy\", \"notes\": \"Algebra\"}\n    response = client.post(\"/sessions/add\", data=data, follow_redirects=True)\n    assert response.status_code == 200\n    assert b\"Math\" in response.data\n\ndef test_add_session_invalid_data(client):\n    \"\"\"POSTing negative minutes should return an error.\"\"\"\n    data = {\"topic\": \"Math\", \"minutes\": \"-5\", \"mood\": \"Sad\", \"notes\": \"\"}\n    response = client.post(\"/sessions/add\", data=data)\n    assert response.status_code == 400\n    assert b\"Minutes must be positive\" in response.data\n\ndef test_demo_reset_seeds_data(client):\n    \"\"\"The demo-reset endpoint should populate the store with initial data.\"\"\"\n    client.post(\"/demo-reset\", follow_redirects=True)\n    response = client.get(\"/sessions\")\n    assert b\"Python\" in response.data\n    assert b\"Flask\" in response.data\n```", "model": "gemini/gemini-3-flash-preview"}}}
